   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_ Princeton_1835-02_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <name type="place" ref="Id_where"/> Edgeworth town
                  <date when="1835-02-16"/>Feb <hi rend = "superscript"> y </hi> 16 <hi rend = "superscript">th</hi> 1835</dateline>
               <salute>
                  <persName>
                     Gentlemen
                  </persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>Your having directed your letter and <lb/>
               parcel of books to <unclear>Jn</unclear> <hi rend = "superscript">t</hi>  Butlers <unclear>Trim</unclear>instead<lb/>
               of to my usual place of residence must<lb/>
               unavoidably occasion delay in your<lb/>
               receiving my answer -- your letter I have<lb/>
               this morning received: the parcel of books<lb/>
               has not yet been forwarded to me -- And<lb/>
               as you desire that if I cannot comply<lb/>
               with your request I should return<lb/>
               the volume by the cheapest conveyance<lb/>
               to <unclear>Mcfs</unclear>.<hi rend = "superscript"><unclear>n</unclear></hi> Curry &amp; C<hi rend = "superscript">o</hi> Dublin I have desired<lb/>
               my brother in law <persName ref="./Personography.xml#ButlX1">Mr Butler</persName> to have<lb/>
               this done --<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>
               I have declined all proposals<lb/>
               to revise or edite works, <del>and to give opinions</del><lb/>
               <del>as to the publishing <add>or republishing</add> of books,</del> <del><unclear></unclear></del><lb/>
               or (,<del>to use your expression</del> <hi rend = "underline">to stand</hi><lb/>
               "<hi rend = "underline">godmother</hi>" to any other persons works,<lb/>
               feeling it quite sufficient responsibility<lb/>
               to answer for my own. This being my<lb/>
               <hi rend = "underline">general</hi>and <hi rend = "underline">fixed</hi> principle I think it<lb/>
               best to say so, <add>to you</add>without looking at the <choice><orig>parti-<lb/>
                  -cular </orig><reg>particular</reg></choice>works in question, because its merits<lb/>
            </p>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_ Princeton_1835-02_page02.jpg"/>
            <p>could not induce me to change my<lb/>
               determination; and my declining your<lb/>
               proposal for these peculiar reasons of my<lb/>
               own cannot give any offence to the authors<lb/>
               or damp the ardor of your scheme<lb/>
            </p>
            <p><del>In which <unclear></unclear>project I wish you</del><lb/>
               <del><unclear></unclear></del><add>I not only wish you success but think</add> think it very likely you will<lb/>
               both succeed and deserve to succeed <add>so</add> from<lb/>
               several specimens I have seen of American<lb/>
               books for children, <add>many of</add> which are ingenious<lb/>
               and interesting from the novelty of<lb/>
               the scenes &amp; manners &amp; from the simplicity<lb/>
               of the stories-- <add> Gentlemen<lb/>
               You apologise for writing to me without a<lb/>
                  regular introduction but that was unnecessary to</add><lb/>
               You may be assured <del><unclear></unclear></del><lb/>
               that far from being offended by your<lb/>
               application, I am gratified by your<lb/>
               thinking my judgment or my literary<lb/>
               name sufficiently good to make it worth<lb/>
               your while to give yourself this trouble<lb/>
            </p>
            <p>Regretting that I cannot comply with
               your request</p>
            <closer>
               I am Gentlemen<lb/>
               Your obed<hi rend = "superscript">t</hi> Servant<lb/>
               Maria Edgeworth<lb/>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
             <p>I am <del>much</del> obliged for your present of one of<lb/>
                the other books<title>"The Young Christian"</title> -- which<lb/>
                I have desired to be reserved for me as if I under   <lb/>
                
            <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_ Princeton_1835-02_page03.jpg"/>
                stand rightly you meant that at all events I<lb/>
                should keep that-<lb/></p>
               <p>If you publish "<unclear>The weekday day book</unclear>"<lb/>
                  I beg to be a purchaser and that you would<lb/>
                  whenever it is published send a copy for<lb/>
                  me to N<hi rend = "superscript">o</hi>. 1 North Audley Street - to the care<lb/>
                  of M<hi rend = "superscript">rs</hi>. <persName ref="./Personography.xml#WilsL1">
                     <forename>Lestock</forename>
                     <surname>Wilson</surname></persName><unclear>(my sister</unclear><lb/>
               </p>
            </postscript>
            <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_ Princeton_1835-02_page04.jpg"/>
            <note place="bottom">1835
               Feb 16<lb/>
               Copy of ME's<lb/>
               answer<lb/>
               to M<hi rend = "superscript">r</hi> <unclear>Sulby</unclear><lb/></note>
